            <h2>This is the portfolio of Lina Högberg Wahlström</h2>

            <p id="introduction">
                During the years 2020-2023 I studied to become an Information Architect and Front-End Developer at Högskolan Borås in Sweden.
                I have a background in the transportations industry, working as a manager and bus driver, and also working as a personal trainer and group fitness instructor on the side. I am doing a career shift to be able to do something that I am passionate about, and to be able to work with something that I find energizing and inspiring. I am a creative person, and the transportations is a very rigid and rule based industry which had me feeling like I was in the wrong place for my ambition level.
                <br>
                The bachelors program gave me a lot of new skills, and also a more in depth  knowledge in subject I already had an interest in like video animation, graphical design and web development. During the education we have gone through programming languages like HTML, CSS, JavaScript and React, together with relative layout design, content management, SEO, graphic design, branding, text production and editing of visual sources. I learned how to use the Adobe Creative Cloud package, and have mostly been working in Illustrator, After Effects, Audition and Photoshop. 
                <br>
                <br>
                The second year I did a web design project with a real life collaborator, which will be more <span><a id="project_link" href="#project">presented below</a></span>. It was a very educational experience, giving the user centric perspective of a development greater meaning and I learned that the needs of a client is not always what the actual need is. The board of the association that I collaborated with wanted to have a more professional looking webpage with information about their activities, and in the evaluation process I realised that they also had a need for a informational platform and membership forum. I re-design their webpage whith this in mind, and created room for more social media presence and more user-friendly ways of interacting with the coaches, other members and the national and international organisation. 
                <br>
                <br>
                The user-friendly perspective has become a passion of mine, and to be able to bring through a message from a client with different elements of media. It is important to me that the things that I create for other people represent them and the messages that they want to communicate. I feel that it is my job to help my clients to expand their views and show them different versions of what they want, to pin-point the essence of their ambition and needs. I look forward to gaining more experience with different types of clients, to learn how to adapt to their individual brands and demands in their line of work. 
                <br>
                <br>
                Besides my professional career I have a family life with two beautiful children and a very supportive husband. We are an active family that likes to do sports, daily adventures on days off and to hang out and connect. Family is important, and the years of studies have thought me to plan my weeks ahead and have a clear agenda with deadlines and to prioritise. This have made me more focused on the tasks and assignments since time has been made to pay them my full attention. I have also learned to be more disciplined and finding tools that help me be able to disconnect from work and studies to be present with my children when we are together. 
                <br>
                <br>
                My current goal in my career is to get as much experience as possible to find out what I really like to do, what I am good at and what I need to have more practice in. You never stop learning. In the future I see myself as part of a strong development team, with a professional network in the business and making successful deliverables to our clients. 
