                <div>
                    <h4 >School project - Web design</h4>
                    <p><span>Assignment:</span> Find a company to collaboreate with and design or re-design their website.</p>
                    <p><span>Tools used:</span> Adobe XD, Adobe Photoshop, one.com online website-tool, text editor.</p>
                    <p><span>Collaborator:</span> Bushido Akademin IF</p>
                    <p><span>Description:</span> local karate association since 2011 with around 50 members. Their need was to get a more modern website, with general information about the training, the schedule and other relevant information. They wanted a place for new potential members and another for old members. The association was also in need of an updated strategy for social media and search engine optimisation. </p>

                    <h5>Old website:</h5>
                    <p>The old website was a static site, with some yearly changes for announcing session times.<br>
                        In the progress of recreating the webpage a content evaluation took place, to see what could be kept and what should be rewritten. The results gave the knowledge that the texts mostly was about the sport and the origin of kyokushin karate, and less about the association and the members, and the familliarity and sence of connection in the association does not shine through. The website was also bland in the color scheme, not giving the attitude and strong feeling sorrounds the training sessions. An initial survey was sent out to all the members to give them the opportunity to make inputs on what was important to them, since the webpage was supposed to be for them.</p>

                        <div class="img_wrapper">
                            <img class="oldies" src="./Pictures/gamla_index.png" alt="Old webpage's index page">
                            <img class="oldies" src="./Pictures/gamla_kontakt.png" alt="Old webpage's contact page">
                            <img class="oldies" class="webpage_pics" src="./Pictures/gamla_regler.png" alt="Old webpage's rule page">
                        </div>    


                    <h5>New website: <a id="bushido" href="https://bushidoakademin.se">bushidoakademin.se</a></h5>
                    <p>To let the power of the sport take more place in the new website the three traditional colors red, black and white was used. The aim for simplicity in the culture of karate was also a big influencer in the project together with the input from the members and the goal to have a relevant textual content. One big aspect was the need to have a good forum for announcements  of new information, therefor a new Facebook page was created, going from a closed group to an open business Facebook page. The page and the pre existing Instagram page was integrated in the index page of the website, making the first page the most dynamic in nature of all the pages, and making the management of the page less complicated. Some of the most frequently asked questions to the coaches in the association was about the schedule, so to fill this need a Google Calendar was created and also integrated on the index webpage.<br>
                    To make the pages more readable on tablets it was made with a single column layout and the web builder tool used at one.com had a usable mobile view, so the website is also readable on mobile devices. The website was also made with a SEO strategy in mind, to make it more visible on the web.<br> 
                    As a side project, out of scope for the school project, a marketing strategy was created together with videos and footage to upload to social media.<br>
                    One of the goals for the association was to get more new members, and during 2023 they had more than 60 new try out sessions generating in around 40 new members, 2 new beginner classes and 1900 new webpage users with an average engagement time of more then 1 minute (source: Google Analytics). One of the reasons could definitely be more visibility locally through social media ads and a locally strong brand.</p>
                    <p>Click on image to go to page.</p>
